6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">=
here</a><span>, but in short, the TSMC chips in Arizona will cost about 50%=
 more, be a few years behind the chips being produced in Taiwan, and do lit=
tle to prevent a worst-case-scenario China invasion of Taiwan. There are al=
so apparently challenges in attracting the right talent to staff these fact=
ories and relatively serious clashes in management styles between TSMC and =
its American partners.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">So perhaps this really is all a =
show of pomp and circumstance, and these two factories are really just two =
very expensive Biden monuments. Or, perhaps more optimistically, this is a =
flawed but necessary first step in re-shoring American manufacturing capabi=
lities and trying to ensure that we don&#8217;t get caught flat-footed and =
chip-less. </p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
