></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The science continues to progress, and seems to=
 be moving even faster than it did in the past decade, in part due to biolo=
gy&#8217;s intersection with AI. But Harper cautions that our infrastructur=
e, specifically enrolling enough people in studies to make sure the drugs a=
ctually work, may continue to be a big bottleneck. </p><p style=3D"color: #=
404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We love us=
 some innovation here at Not Boring, but this piece is a reminder that the =
infrastructure is often just as important. The innovations don&#8217;t matt=
er if they don&#8217;t get to market. Harper put it well:</p><blockquote st=
yle=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 20px 0;"><p style=3D"color: =
